name: Devworks Collective
description: A global online community for aspiring and practicing developers to learn JavaScript, share projects, get feedback, and grow together through weekly challenges, AMAs, and collaborative coding sessions.
address: Montes Urales 424, Lomas de Chapultepec, 11000 Ciudad de México, CDMX

name: LaunchCode Guild
description: An invite-only online community for mid-level developers preparing for senior roles. Includes bi-weekly code deep dives, resume workshops, mock interviews, and direct access to engineering managers at top tech companies.

name: First Commit
description: A welcoming, zero-cost community for total beginners learning to code. Daily check-ins, friendly project feedback, and guided JavaScript/HTML/CSS challenges—no experience needed. Built on kindness, not competition.

name: Pixel & Code
description: Where designers learn to code and developers discover design. A vibrant online space for building interactive portfolios, creative coding projects (p5.js, Three.js), and collaborative art-tech experiments.
